學科別分類



中文摘要

                  在調查瞭解對電腦頻繁使用的狀況下，以現今電腦教室教學空間之新鮮外氣換氣效率不佳導致室內空氣品質嚴重問題為研究主軸，本研究以電腦教室單元空間為探討對象，針對不同空調系統通風設置模式，考量室內換氣效率與溫熱環境之健康性及舒適性，以機械通風及增設地板抽風模式進行探討。藉由不同出風設置搭配地板抽風模式對應不同風速之設定而做調變，以追求效率為原則，達到「健康性」及「舒適性」之目的，探討何種搭配方式為較佳出風之設置方式。本研究以樹德科技大學設計學院之專業電腦教室作為實驗標的，透過室內環境品質標準量測即是進行標準狀態環境檢討，並以實測之最佳模式作為探討多樣出回風路徑之CFD數值模擬解析方式之設定，以可視化結果檢討室內溫度場、氣流場之路徑與分佈並據以提出出風口最佳化之模式。本研究希望能在健康、舒適需求之間求得較佳平衡點，以供未來電腦教室於室內出風口設置配套設計使用上之參考，期能為改善電腦教室室內空氣品質與空調出風設置之設計參考。本研究之研究目的及方法分述如下：	研究目的一、	探討不同空調系統出風模式對電腦教室換氣效率與溫熱環境之影響二、	探討在搭配地板抽風模式下，對室內溫度分佈、污染物濃度排除、氣流環境等影響。三、	比對足尺實驗與數值模擬結果之客觀性四、	建立最佳化結果之預測，建構健康性及舒適性之檢索。	研究方法一、	本研究選定以樹德科技大學室內設計系電腦教室環境條件控制設定，其空間尺寸為1070㎝×989㎝×335㎝作為探討空間。二、	根據電腦教室環境條件下，歸納分析改善前後之不同空調系統出風模式進行實測，透過應用統計分析方法，綜合評估室內換氣效率與溫熱環境（健康性、舒適性），將結果轉換成較佳搭配使用之出風設置設計的參考設定，提出應用混合通風對應出風設置策略進行模擬設定。三、	本研究運用CFD數值解析方式進行室內穩態氣流場、溫度場之解析結果，並利用電腦進行室內環境可視化分析。 	研究結果1.	本研究問捲統計結果針對室內空氣之新鮮度及整體空氣品質兩項中皆有10%之不滿意分佈，比對其實測空間中所得PPD數據為9.3%不滿意分佈，驗證實測數據及問捲調查之準確性。2.	在室內人數在33人中不滿意程度為9.3%（模組E），在16人中不滿意程度為12.5%（模組H），在10人中不滿意程度為13.5%（模組B），可見其空間室容積與室內人員密度及風速設定大小皆有相關的影響性。3.	在電腦教室改善前後皆有設置高架地板，但不同的是改善後之空間增加了地板抽風口及抽風機，以及增設了新鮮外氣引氣口，有效增加了室內空氣的新鮮度以及室內污染物的排除效果。4.	在改善後之室內無人使用條件下搭配地板抽風開關的設定中，發現地板抽風開啟模組之換氣率皆優於地板抽風關閉模組。5.	在室內有人使用之條件搭配地板抽風開啟的設定中，發現有人之換氣率皆高於無人，可確定室內有人使用增加室內空氣混合率。6.	室內CO2濃度的高低，主要受到人員密度與風速大小設定、地板抽風開關差異所影響。在有人使用CO2/人之增量值計算與地板抽風開啟的設定所呈現的結果發現，增設高架地板抽風可將隔天教室內CO2濃度降到最低，增加了室內換氣有效度。7.	綜合建議：在具備均勻分佈之抽風口後將地板抽風開啟，其室內換氣率最高，而以預測模組探討之，在考量「健康性」、「舒適性」及提昇整體環境效率上，以模組C-1-4之出風設置設計為較佳整合方案。



英文摘要

                  Through the investigation of the frequent computer usage, it is understood that the poor efficiency of fresh outdoor air exchange in the computer classroom has resulted in a serious issue of indoor air quality. This study targeted on a single computer room and aimed to discuss different ventilation models of the air conditioning facility as well as the machine ventilation and the additional floor exhaust ventilation concerning about the indoor air exchange efficiency and the healthiness and comfortability of hot environment. Further, this study also discussed which combination model can provide a better ventilation facility through the modulation of different floor exhaust models with their corresponding wind velocity setup in order to achieve the objective of “healthiness” and “comfortability” on the basis of the efficiency principal. The computer classroom of the College of Design of Shu-Te University was taken as sample for experiment. After the standard evaluation of the indoor environment quality, this study immediately conducted a review on the standard environment condition, used the best testing model to discuss the setup of the CFD numerical simulation of the multiple return air routes, and reviewed the routes and distribution of the indoor temperature flow and flow of air current based on the visual results to propose the optimum fan model. It is hoped to provide references for the interior fan design for future computer classroom as well as for improving the designs of indoor air quality in the computer classroom and the exhaust fan installation.	Research objectives1. Discuss the impact of different air-conditioning and ventilation models on the air exchange efficiency and hot environment.2. Discuss the impact of the floor exhaust fan model on the room temperature distribution, exhausted contaminant concentration and environment of air current.  3. Establish an optimum result prediction and construct a search for healthiness and comfortability.	Research methods1. This study targeted on the environment control setup in the computer room of the College of Design of Shu-Te University. The size of the space is 1070 cm×989 cm×335 cm.2. Based on the environment condition in the computer room, this study analyzed the exhaust fan model of different air-conditioning systems and conducted an experimental test before and after the improvement. Through the statistic analysis method and overall evaluation of the indoor air exchange efficiency and hot environment (healthiness and comfortability), the result was taken as references for designing a better exhaust fan setup. Besides, the strategy of applying mixed ventilation to correspond the respective exhaust fan setup was proposed for the implementation of simulation setup. 3. Through the CFD numerical analysis method, this study further analyzed the indoor static air current and temperature flow, and used the computer room to conduct the indoor environment visual analysis.	Research results1. According to the result of the survey-questionnaire about the freshness of the indoor air and overall air quality, 10% of the distribution was not satisfied comparing to 9.3% of the PRD data from the experimental test. This further proved the accuracy of both experimental test and survey-questionnaire.2. When no people in the room, it is found that the air exchange rate of the opened floor exhaust fan module works better than the closed floor exhaust fan module after the improvement.3. When someone is using the floor exhaust fan in the room, it is found that the air exchange rate is better. The results can be conducted as the air mix rate increases when someone is using the floor exhaust fan indoor. 4. The CO2 concentration level is mainly affected by the degree of wind velocity and the switch of the floor exhaust fan. According to the calculation of CO2/person incremental value and the result of the unlocked setup of the floor exhaust fan, it is found that the newly setup of the elevated floor exhaust fan can minimize the CO2 concentration on the next day and increase the efficiency of the indoor air exchange.5. General recommendations: the indoor air exchange rate is optimum when opening the floor exhaust fan once the air of the exhaust vent is normally distributed. Concerning the “healthiness” and “comfortability” as well as the improvement of the overall environment efficiency, the ventilation design of module C-1-4 is considered a better integrated proposal.



